572
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:05,200
 >> The UK Ministry of Defense is an organization broadly analogous

573
00:34:05,200 --> 00:34:09,200
 to the US Department of Defense and has a dual role both

574
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:11,760
 as a policymaking department of state

575
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:15,200
 and as the UK's highest level military headquarters.

576
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:19,760
 I worked there for 21 years as a civilian, three of which were

577
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:22,600
 spent on MOD's UFO project.

578
00:34:22,600 --> 00:34:27,080
 That's a job I had from 1991 to 1994.

579
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:32,960
 The MOD's UFO project ran from 1953 to 2009 and in that time,

580
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:36,520
 over 12,000 sightings were investigated.

581
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:40,400
 MOD's role here was to research and investigate the phenomenon

582
00:34:40,400 --> 00:34:43,360
 to determine whether there was evidence of any potential threat

583
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,760
 to the defense of the UK or anything

584
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:49,160
 of more general defense interest.

585
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:52,960
 The UK's interest in UFOs had its roots in concerns

586
00:34:52,960 --> 00:34:56,000
 that some objects might be foreign military aircraft

587
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,960
 on reconnaissance missions or on missions

588
00:34:58,960 --> 00:35:02,120
 to test the capabilities and effectiveness

589
00:35:02,120 --> 00:35:05,560
 of our air defense network, both in terms of radar

590
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:07,800
 and air defense aircraft.

591
00:35:07,800 --> 00:35:10,040
 The work we did was very similar to the work done

592
00:35:10,040 --> 00:35:12,760
 by the US government's UFO program embedded

593
00:35:12,760 --> 00:35:15,560
 in the United States Air Force under a number

594
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:16,880
 of different project names,

595
00:35:16,880 --> 00:35:19,560
 the best known of which was Project Blue Book.

596
00:35:19,560 --> 00:35:23,840
 The UK's program had no formal project name.

597
00:35:23,840 --> 00:35:27,440
 Our conclusions were that most sightings could be explained

598
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:31,000
 as misidentifications of known objects or phenomena.

599
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:35,720
 However, around 5% appeared to defy conventional explanation

600
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:38,120
 and were of considerable interest.

601
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:41,600
 We took no position on the nature of these sightings

602
00:35:41,600 --> 00:35:45,080
 and remained open-minded as to the possibilities.

603
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:47,800
 Accordingly, while we were aware of no evidence

604
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:49,320
 that would support the theory

605
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:51,800
 that any UFO sightings were attributable

606
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:54,800
 to extraterrestrial life, we didn't entirely rule

607
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:56,640
 out that possibility.

608
00:35:56,640 --> 00:36:01,200
 It was regarded as a low-probability, high-consequence

609
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:04,560
 scenario, which is why from time to time the possibility was

610
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:09,280
 at least considered in internal MOD discussions.

611
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:12,840
 Despite the wider societal implications,

612
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:15,000
 MOD's interest was narrowly focused

613
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:17,120
 on technology acquisition.

614
00:36:17,120 --> 00:36:20,400
 Scientific and technical intelligence experts

615
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:24,360
 in MOD's defense intelligence staff were not averse

616
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:27,640
 to speculating about exotic energy sources,

617
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:31,840
 propulsion systems or aerodynamics in relation to UFOs.

618
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:34,360
 And perhaps the most graphic illustration

619
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:37,040
 of this was a defense intelligence staff document

620
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:41,680
 from 1995 which read in part, "If the sightings are

621
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:44,720
 of devices not of this earth, then their purpose needs

622
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:47,280
 to be established as a matter of priority.

623
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:50,200
 There has been no apparent hostile intent

624
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:54,320
 and other possibilities are, one, military reconnaissance,

625
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:58,800
 two, scientific, three, tourism."

626
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:00,800
 [ Laughter ]

627
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:04,800
 The intent was practical as the document went on to set out,

628
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:09,200
 quote, "We could use this technology if it exists."

629
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:12,160
 Though we accepted UFO reports from everyone,

630
00:37:12,160 --> 00:37:15,520
 and indeed the vast majority of those reports came to us

631
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:18,800
 from the public, the sightings that were of most interest were

632
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:22,000
 those where the witnesses were police officers, pilots,

633
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,960
 or military personnel.

634
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:27,160
 And when I say pilots, I mean both civil aircraft pilots

635
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:29,640
 and military pilots.

636
00:37:29,640 --> 00:37:31,840
 We were also particularly interested in sightings

637
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:33,600
 where there was some corroborative evidence,

638
00:37:33,600 --> 00:37:37,520
 e.g. in terms of radar data or a photograph or film

639
00:37:37,520 --> 00:37:41,360
 that specialist imagery analysis staff could evaluate.

640
00:37:41,360 --> 00:37:44,800
 Of particular concern to us were a number of incidents

641
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:46,080
 where there were near misses

642
00:37:46,080 --> 00:37:48,720
 between UFOs and commercial aircraft.

643
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,960
 There are several such cases in the MOD's UFO files

644
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:54,840
 and in the files of the Civil Aviation Authority,

645
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:57,320
 which is a UK government agency broadly equivalent

646
00:37:57,320 --> 00:38:00,040
 to the US FAA.

647
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:03,240
 The UK's best known and most compelling UFO incident is a

648
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:06,520
 series of sightings that occurred in December 1980,

649
00:38:06,520 --> 00:38:09,240
 collectively known as either the Rendlesham Forest incident

650
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:10,880
 or the Bentwaters incident,

651
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:15,120
 and the committee has already taken evidence on this.

652
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:19,280
 In the late '90s, the MOD's defense intelligence staff

653
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:22,040
 commissioned a review of many of the UFO sightings

654
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:24,560
 that MOD had investigated over the years.

655
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:28,280
 This intelligence analysis was known as Project Condyne,

656
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:31,040
 which was a randomly generated code word.

657
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:34,960
 And this attempted some trend analysis of the reports received

658
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:39,640
 as opposed to reinvestigation of individual cases.

659
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:43,040
 The final report was published in the year 2000 and ran

660
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:45,040
 to over 400 pages.

661
00:38:45,040 --> 00:38:47,880
 The title was Unidentified Aerial Phenomena

662
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:50,560
 in the UK Air Defense Region.

663
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:53,280
 The MOD often uses the phrase UAP,

664
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:57,640
 Unidentified Aerial Phenomena, in internal correspondence,

665
00:38:57,640 --> 00:38:59,880
 so as to avoid the unfortunate stigma

666
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:02,520
 that comes from the term UFO.

667
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:06,280
 At the time, Project Condyne's final report was classified

668
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:08,600
 secret UK eyes only.

669
00:39:08,600 --> 00:39:10,320
 Its controversial conclusion was

670
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:13,200
 that some UFO sightings might be attributable

671
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:16,080
 to exotic atmospheric plasmas,

672
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:19,080
 and that there might be novel military applications,

673
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:21,760
 e.g. in terms of directed energy weapons,

674
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:24,160
 that might merit further study.

675
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:26,520
 Again, the air safety implications

676
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:29,240
 of the phenomenon were judged to be an important part,

677
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:32,400
 and one recommendation of the study read as follows,

678
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:36,320
 no attempt should be made to outmaneuver a UAP

679
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:38,440
 during interception.

680
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:42,360
 Another recommendation stated, at higher altitudes,

681
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:46,440
 although UAP appear to be benign to civil air traffic,

682
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:49,400
 pilots should be advised not to maneuver other

683
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:52,720
 than to place the object astern if possible.

684
00:39:52,720 --> 00:39:56,480
 A redacted version of Project Condyne's final report was made

685
00:39:56,480 --> 00:40:00,320
 available to the public in May 2006, following a number

686
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:03,400
 of Freedom of Information Act requests.

687
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:06,800
 There is in the UK, as in the US, a widely held belief

688
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:09,040
 that the authorities know more about UFOs

689
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:11,480
 than they're telling the public, i.e. that there's a coverup

690
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:13,640
 and a conspiracy on the subject.

691
00:40:13,640 --> 00:40:16,520
 I think there are two relevant factors here.

692
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:20,520
 Firstly, the MOD was and still is an inherently secretive

693
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:22,800
 organization despite the introduction

694
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:25,480
 of the UK's Freedom of Information Act.

695
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:29,040
 Secondly, it was the longstanding policy of the MOD

696
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:32,520
 to downplay the extent of the department's interest

697
00:40:32,520 --> 00:40:35,680
 and the scope of our official research and investigation,

698
00:40:35,680 --> 00:40:38,440
 not all of which, especially post-Freedom

699
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:41,160
 of Information Act, generated the paper trail

700
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:43,760
 that one might expect and hope for.

701
00:40:43,760 --> 00:40:45,880
 To give a practical example of this,

702
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:48,960
 we consistently told the UK's Parliament, the media

703
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:52,440
 and the public that UFOs were of limited interest

704
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:56,480
 and "no defense significance,"

705
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:59,440
 while highly classified intelligence studies

706
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:01,760
 such as Project Condyne were being carried

707
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:04,320
 out away from public scrutiny.

708
00:41:04,320 --> 00:41:08,360
 That said, despite the secrecy and despite the downplaying

709
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:12,160
 of MOD's UFO-related work, I'm not aware of any coverup

710
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:14,560
 or conspiracy in the sense that proponents

711
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,800
 of such theories mean.

712
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:20,800
 MOD's UFO project was terminated in 2009 as part

713
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,360
 of a wider series of defense cuts,

714
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:26,160
 and while the public no longer have an official point

715
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:30,320
 of contact for their sightings, pilots can and do continue

716
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,560
 to make reports on an ad hoc basis, though they tend

717
00:41:33,560 --> 00:41:37,440
 to avoid the phrase UFO or indeed UAP.

718
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:40,480
 And in my experience now tend to use phrases

719
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,800
 such as "unusual aircraft."

720
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:48,080
 In 2007, the MOD made a policy decision to declassify

721
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:51,160
 and release its entire archive of UFO files,

722
00:41:51,160 --> 00:41:52,880
 following a similar decision made

723
00:41:52,880 --> 00:41:56,040
 by the French government in 2007.

724
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:57,640
 This five-year program,

725
00:41:57,640 --> 00:42:00,360
 in which I've been personally involved, began with the release

726
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:03,680
 of the first batch of files in May 2008.

727
00:42:03,680 --> 00:42:05,520
 Subsequent batches followed,

728
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:08,840
 and the program reaches its climax this year.

729
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:12,920
 To date, over 50,000 pages of documents have been sent

730
00:42:12,920 --> 00:42:15,000
 to the UK's National Archives.

731
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,640
 The UK and France are two of a number of nations

732
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:21,120
 that have opened their UFO files recently in response to pressure

733
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,840
 from media and the public, and again,

734
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:25,320
 the committee's had some testimony on that.

735
00:42:25,320 --> 00:42:27,400
 In concluding, I should say

736
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:32,120
 that I do not have a single neat explanation for the UFO mystery,

737
00:42:32,120 --> 00:42:33,840
 and neither am I aware that anyone

738
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:37,920
 in the UK government has or had reached a definitive conclusion.

739
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:41,280
 However, having undertaken three years

740
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:44,400
 of official UK government research and investigation

741
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:48,600
 into the UFO phenomenon, my belief, my assessment,

742
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,760
 is that whatever the true nature of the phenomenon,

743
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:54,040
 it raises important defense, national security,

744
00:42:54,040 --> 00:42:55,800
 and air safety issues.

745
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:59,960
 Additionally, as pointed out in Project Condine's final report,

746
00:42:59,960 --> 00:43:03,440
 there are potential novel technology applications

747
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:05,560
 and military applications that may result

748
00:43:05,560 --> 00:43:08,840
 from a proper scientific study of the phenomenon.

749
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:12,360
 And finally, and perhaps most importantly in relation

750
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:15,800
 to this event, and I think we heard it most graphically

751
00:43:15,800 --> 00:43:18,800
 with the testimony from Sergeants Penniston and Burroughs

752
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:21,440
 and their ongoing quest for their medical records,

753
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:24,800
 I think it's clear that, again, whatever the nature

754
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:27,760
 of this phenomenon and this mystery, there are issues

755
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:30,440
 of political accountability, open government,

756
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:32,160
 and freedom of information here.

757
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,480
 Thank you.

