00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:01,880
 by the French government.

788
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:06,200
 In 1974, the Minister of Defense, Robert Galli,

789
00:45:06,200 --> 00:45:09,720
 admitted in a famous radio interview that, quote,

790
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:11,680
 "The massive reports coming

791
00:45:11,680 --> 00:45:15,280
 in from the gendarmerie were pretty disturbing."

792
00:45:15,280 --> 00:45:19,000
 The minister added that, quote, "I believe that the attitude

793
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:23,120
 of spirit that we must adopt vis-a-vis the phenomenon is an

794
00:45:23,120 --> 00:45:26,760
 open one, that is to say that it doesn't consist

795
00:45:26,760 --> 00:45:29,400
 in denying a priori as our ancestors

796
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:33,160
 of previous centuries did deny many things

797
00:45:33,160 --> 00:45:38,120
 that seem nowadays perfectly elementary," end quote.

798
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:41,640
 The National Gendarmerie, which is a national police force,

799
00:45:41,640 --> 00:45:43,800
 similar to our state troopers,

800
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:47,120
 had been investigating UFO incidents since the '60s,

801
00:45:47,120 --> 00:45:50,040
 including a famous UFO landing and close encounter

802
00:45:50,040 --> 00:45:53,720
 of the third kind, CE-3, cases where humanoid beings

803
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:57,080
 or UFO occupants are seen in connection with the sighting

804
00:45:57,080 --> 00:46:00,160
 in Val-en-Salle in 1965.

805
00:46:00,160 --> 00:46:05,040
 Ten years later, the gendarmerie formalized its UFO protocols

806
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:07,680
 by issuing instructions that gendarmes

807
00:46:07,680 --> 00:46:11,000
 throughout the French territory, including those overseas

808
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,360
 like French Guyana or Reunion Island

809
00:46:13,360 --> 00:46:15,840
 in the Indian Ocean, should respond

810
00:46:15,840 --> 00:46:19,960
 and investigate any UFO incident reported by French citizens.

811
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:23,200
 These protocols are still current.

812
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:28,200
 In 1977, the Institute of High Studies of National Defense,

813
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:33,160
 or IHEDN, a key think tank of the French military,

814
00:46:33,160 --> 00:46:36,960
 released an important study which recommended establishment

815
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:40,120
 of a permanent agency to study UFOs.

816
00:46:40,120 --> 00:46:43,640
 This was accomplished later that year when the CNAS,

817
00:46:43,640 --> 00:46:46,960
 the French space agency equivalent to our NASA,

818
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:51,040
 created the study group of unidentified aerospace phenomena,

819
00:46:51,040 --> 00:46:55,440
 GEPAN, under the direction of aerospace engineer Claude Poher,

820
00:46:55,440 --> 00:46:57,920
 who had conducted UFO research on his own

821
00:46:57,920 --> 00:46:59,640
 for a number of years.

822
00:46:59,640 --> 00:47:03,440
 One of his first tasks was to conduct a statistical study

823
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:08,840
 of 354 UFO cases collected by the gendarmerie, 25%

824
00:47:08,840 --> 00:47:12,440
 of which remained unexplained.

825
00:47:12,440 --> 00:47:15,480
 On the morning of January 8, 1981,

826
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:18,400
 GEPAN's most important case took place.

827
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:22,400
 A UFO landed on the property of a farmer in Transan-Provence

828
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:25,240
 in the Valle region of southwest France.

829
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:27,560
 Although the case had only one witness,

830
00:47:27,560 --> 00:47:32,280
 the farmer Renato Nicolai, the case became important

831
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:35,120
 because of the physical evidence left by the UFO

832
00:47:35,120 --> 00:47:38,440
 on the alfalfa field, which was analyzed scientifically

833
00:47:38,440 --> 00:47:41,000
 by a number of French laboratories.

834
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:45,160
 Among other things, the alfalfa leaves lost from 30

835
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:49,680
 to 50% of chlorophyll, and the traces on the terrain were still

836
00:47:49,680 --> 00:47:52,480
 perceptible 40 days after the event,

837
00:47:52,480 --> 00:47:54,720
 according to the official report.

838
00:47:54,720 --> 00:47:59,240
 Stranger still was what an official GEPAN chart--

839
00:47:59,240 --> 00:48:01,280
 and I don't know if we have it on the--

840
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:03,600
 I had given it previously, so hopefully it

841
00:48:03,600 --> 00:48:05,840
 will appear on the screen, the chart.

842
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:09,360
 Stranger was what an official GEPAN chart characterized

843
00:48:09,360 --> 00:48:12,600
 as, quote, "time-space effect."

844
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:15,400
 Professor Buaz, one of the scientists who conducted

845
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:19,480
 the analysis, explained that while the plants were

846
00:48:19,480 --> 00:48:23,400
 physiologically young, after the UFO landing,

847
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:25,720
 they presented-- and I'm quoting now--

848
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:28,360
 "the biochemical characteristics of leaves

849
00:48:28,360 --> 00:48:31,200
 of an advanced age," old leaves.

850
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:33,440
 So in other words, they were young plants.

851
00:48:33,440 --> 00:48:37,000
 After the UFO landed, they became biochemically old.

852
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:39,080
 And that, according to the scientists,

853
00:48:39,080 --> 00:48:41,320
 doesn't happen in nature.

854
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:43,480
 The final conclusion of the GEPAN chart

855
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:47,720
 was, quote, "physical phenomenon of unexplained nature,

856
00:48:47,720 --> 00:48:50,600
 high probability of electromagnetic mode

857
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:52,640
 of propulsion."

858
00:48:52,640 --> 00:48:55,240
 Despite this and other significant cases

859
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:57,840
 investigated and documented by GEPAN,

860
00:48:57,840 --> 00:49:00,760
 the agency was downgraded in the mid-'80s,

861
00:49:00,760 --> 00:49:03,040
 and the name was changed to SEPRA,

862
00:49:03,040 --> 00:49:06,480
 an acronym for the Reentry of Atmospheric Objects.

863
00:49:06,480 --> 00:49:09,780
 Although the agency continued to investigate UFO cases

864
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:12,240
 under the direction of Jean-Jacques Velasco, who

865
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:16,160
 was the case investigator of the Trans-Improvance incident.

866
00:49:16,160 --> 00:49:20,800
 In 2007, however, a new reorganization took place,

867
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:23,720
 and the name was changed again to GEPAN--

868
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:25,440
 so they added an I there--

869
00:49:25,440 --> 00:49:29,720
 Study and Information Group of Unidentified Aerospace

870
00:49:29,720 --> 00:49:30,920
 Phenomena.

871
00:49:30,920 --> 00:49:34,440
 GEPAN also launched a comprehensive website

872
00:49:34,440 --> 00:49:36,240
 and began the process of releasing

873
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:38,280
 all of its documents, which are now

874
00:49:38,280 --> 00:49:41,040
 available within the CNS portal.

875
00:49:41,040 --> 00:49:43,600
 That's the French Space Agency.

876
00:49:43,600 --> 00:49:47,560
 Parallel to the official GEPAN and gendarmerie investigations,

877
00:49:47,560 --> 00:49:51,040
 there has also been some highly interesting semi-official

878
00:49:51,040 --> 00:49:54,680
 reports from groups connected to the French military,

879
00:49:54,680 --> 00:49:57,920
 intelligence, and aeronautical establishment.

880
00:49:57,920 --> 00:50:02,000
 The first and most famous one was the so-called cometa report

881
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:06,300
 of 1999, entitled UFOs and Defense--

882
00:50:06,300 --> 00:50:08,600
 What Should We Prepare For?

883
00:50:08,600 --> 00:50:10,680
 Although not an official government report

884
00:50:10,680 --> 00:50:13,080
 in the strict sense of the word, cometa

885
00:50:13,080 --> 00:50:16,040
 was composed of a group of retired, high ranking

886
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:18,280
 military and intelligence officers

887
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:21,880
 under the direction of retired Major General Dennis Letty.

888
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:25,280
 Their conclusion that UFOs were definitely real and most

889
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:29,720
 likely of extraterrestrial origin were very strong.

890
00:50:29,720 --> 00:50:33,240
 More recently, another quasi-official organization,

891
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:37,360
 the 3AF, which stands for the Aeronautical and Astronomical

892
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:40,560
 Association of France, created a high level study

893
00:50:40,560 --> 00:50:42,800
 group known as the Sigma Commission

894
00:50:42,800 --> 00:50:45,240
 under the direction of Alain Boudier.

895
00:50:45,240 --> 00:50:48,080
 Sigma has recently completed a long report,

896
00:50:48,080 --> 00:50:50,880
 again confirming the existence of a real UFO

897
00:50:50,880 --> 00:50:54,040
 phenomenon of likely ET origin.

898
00:50:54,040 --> 00:50:57,060
 From all of this material briefly outlined

899
00:50:57,060 --> 00:50:59,880
 in this presentation, you can see that the French are

900
00:50:59,880 --> 00:51:01,760
 undoubtedly among the leading nations

901
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:04,080
 to conduct significant UFO research,

902
00:51:04,080 --> 00:51:06,640
 both officially and semi-officially.

903
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:09,200
 Instead of burying their heads in the sand,

904
00:51:09,200 --> 00:51:11,920
 pretending that a UFO phenomenon doesn't exist

905
00:51:11,920 --> 00:51:15,520
 or is not important, France, the cradle of rationalism

906
00:51:15,520 --> 00:51:18,720
 in the modern era, have taken an aggressive approach

907
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:22,260
 towards solving this phenomenon.

908
00:51:22,260 --> 00:51:25,680
 Let me outline now very briefly the history of UFO research

909
00:51:25,680 --> 00:51:28,360
 in Russia and the old Soviet Union.

910
00:51:28,360 --> 00:51:32,080
 In the early days of communism, the subject of UFOs

911
00:51:32,080 --> 00:51:35,320
 was heavily censored, although some research was conducted

912
00:51:35,320 --> 00:51:39,120
 privately by a few scientists, such as the late Professor

913
00:51:39,120 --> 00:51:43,320
 Felix Siegel, an astronomer with the Moscow Aviation Institute

914
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:46,720
 who is considered the father of Russian ufology.

915
00:51:46,720 --> 00:51:50,280
 Things began to change after a highly publicized event

916
00:51:50,280 --> 00:51:54,040
 in Petrosovodsk in Karelia, northern Russia in September

917
00:51:54,040 --> 00:51:58,000
 of 1977, which led to the creation of a commission

918
00:51:58,000 --> 00:52:01,720
 for the study of anomalous phenomena attached to the USSR

919
00:52:01,720 --> 00:52:03,520
 Academy of Sciences.

920
00:52:03,520 --> 00:52:06,640
 This commission was public since it solicited reports

921
00:52:06,640 --> 00:52:08,640
 from the Soviet citizenry.

922
00:52:08,640 --> 00:52:10,840
 Not known to the public, however,

923
00:52:10,840 --> 00:52:13,280
 was the second secret study conducted

924
00:52:13,280 --> 00:52:16,680
 by the KGB and the Soviet Ministry of Defense,

925
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:19,600
 although its existence was not revealed

926
00:52:19,600 --> 00:52:23,960
 until after the breakdown of the USSR in 1990.

927
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:27,680
 Eventually, some military and KGB files from this commission

928
00:52:27,680 --> 00:52:30,000
 were released in the '90s, including

929
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:35,560
 incidents involving UFO flyings over nuclear facilities.

930
00:52:35,560 --> 00:52:38,660
 One of the most interesting cases in the KGB file

931
00:52:38,660 --> 00:52:42,600
 is a multiple witness CE-1 close encounter of the first kind

932
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:45,040
 at a top secret army missile base

933
00:52:45,040 --> 00:52:48,320
 in the district of Kapustin Yar, Astrakhan region,

934
00:52:48,320 --> 00:52:52,440
 on the night of July 28, 29, 1989.

935
00:52:52,440 --> 00:52:55,240
 The file is surely incomplete, but still

936
00:52:55,240 --> 00:52:58,280
 offers an interesting glimpse into the maneuverability

937
00:52:58,280 --> 00:52:59,720
 of UFOs.

938
00:52:59,720 --> 00:53:01,920
 The dossier consists of the depositions

939
00:53:01,920 --> 00:53:05,120
 of seven military witnesses, two junior officers,

940
00:53:05,120 --> 00:53:08,680
 a corporal, and four privates, plus illustrations

941
00:53:08,680 --> 00:53:12,120
 of the object by the observers and a briefcase summary

942
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:14,680
 by an unnamed KGB officer.

943
00:53:14,680 --> 00:53:18,400
 One of the depositions mentions a disc-shaped object moving,

944
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:22,760
 quote, "in the direction of the rocket's weapons depot,"

945
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:27,680
 and then hovering over the depot and emitting a bright beam.

946
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:30,640
 Another case from 1982 involved a series

947
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:33,160
 of sightings of UFOs over a nuclear missile

948
00:53:33,160 --> 00:53:37,000
 base near Usovo, Ukraine, which coincided

949
00:53:37,000 --> 00:53:39,680
 with the malfunction of the computerized console

950
00:53:39,680 --> 00:53:42,080
 controlling the launch of nuclear weapons.

951
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:45,320
 This was obviously of great concern to the Soviet military,

952
00:53:45,320 --> 00:53:48,120
 and is quite similar to the events at Malmstrom Air Force

953
00:53:48,120 --> 00:53:53,080
 Base in Montana discussed in another session of these hearings.

954
00:53:53,080 --> 00:53:56,120
 It is perhaps due to these kinds of incidents involving

955
00:53:56,120 --> 00:53:59,720
 nuclear weapons that a curious clause about, quote,

956
00:53:59,720 --> 00:54:03,960
 "unidentified objects" was added to an agreement on measures

957
00:54:03,960 --> 00:54:06,240
 to reduce the risk of nuclear war

958
00:54:06,240 --> 00:54:08,080
 between the United States of America

959
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:10,960
 and the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics.

960
00:54:10,960 --> 00:54:13,440
 The agreement was part of a policy of detente

961
00:54:13,440 --> 00:54:16,920
 during the Nixon and early Brezhnev administrations.

962
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:19,960
 It was signed on September 30, 1971,

963
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:23,480
 by Secretary of State William Rogers and Foreign Minister

964
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:25,400
 Andrei Gromyko.

965
00:54:25,400 --> 00:54:27,880
 The agreement has nine articles on issues

966
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:30,280
 such as informing each other, quote,

967
00:54:30,280 --> 00:54:33,040
 "against the accidental or unauthorized use

968
00:54:33,040 --> 00:54:35,640
 of nuclear weapons under its control,"

969
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:38,320
 notification in advance of missile launches that

970
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:41,200
 go beyond the national territory of each country,

971
00:54:41,200 --> 00:54:43,320
 and other measures of cooperation

972
00:54:43,320 --> 00:54:47,400
 in order to avert, quote, "the risk of outbreak of nuclear war."

973
00:54:47,400 --> 00:54:51,480
 Article 3 reads, I'm quoting, "the parties undertake

974
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:55,080
 to notify each other immediately in the event of detection

975
00:54:55,080 --> 00:54:59,480
 by missile warning systems of unidentified objects

976
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:02,360
 or in the event of signs of interference

977
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:06,120
 with these systems or with the related communication

978
00:55:06,120 --> 00:55:08,800
 facilities if such occurrences could

979
00:55:08,800 --> 00:55:12,360
 create a risk of outbreak of nuclear war

980
00:55:12,360 --> 00:55:14,440
 between the two countries."

981
00:55:14,440 --> 00:55:17,120
 It's a good thing that they signed this agreement.

982
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:20,160
 Several UFO cases involving Russian cosmonauts

983
